# Create a virtual enviornment
     follow LearnPythonByDoing/Basics/LocalEnviornmentSetup.md to understand about local enviornment.

# Steps for installation
1) Initiate virtual enviornment
2) Install the django-> pip install django
3) Verify the version-> django-admin --version
4) Create a new project directory from cmd-> mkdir Django
5) Start the project-> django-admin startproject Django_project(Project name)
6) Verify the directory structure by -> dir command
        You should have manage.oy and other file inside

7) Go to Project directory Django_project.
8) Start the development server -> python manage.py runserver
      You will get local server URL and port number like this-> http://127.0.0.1:8000/
      Run that local server on the web browser.
      
